Text.Value: You have resisted such a fate so far. And this would be a complete evolution.

Text.Value: I know how big this is to you, but trust me Lae'zel. Trust me.

The prince will be dead. And we will still stand a chance against the Netherbrain. Now - give me the stones.
We will end the Grand Design. And then we will go our separate ways.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: spoken to player only

I told you the githyanki would only want to kill you for what you are.

EditorData.logicalname: LAE'ZEL ORPHEUS PATH & DOESN'T HAVE HAMMER

Text.Value: You will see the world as I do - its truth, its devastating beauty.
Do not speak his name!
Impossible. You have no means of liberating the githyanki prince. If the Netherbrain is to fall, the prince must be assimilated.
You took the devil's deal. And lied to me.
What would happen to me?
Is this really something you would be willing to accept?
I trust the Emperor more than I trust Orpheus.
You will not lay a finger on my kin.
Very well. But when the brain is defeated, the stones return to me.
First, you will feel discomfort. Then - flourishing.
Orpheus is the enemy of my people. I mean to use the Hammer to free him - and kill him.
Hold a moment. We are not so short on time that we cannot stop and think about this.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to slow things down - the player just volunteered to sacrifice themselves, and she's urging us to stop and talk it through with her companions. Projecting calm and reason.

Text.Value: Orpheus is the future of my people. I mean to use the Hammer and set him free.
*You feel Lae'zel's parasite tremble. Her mind speaks directly to yours.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mindmeld

Text.Value: I will consume his thoughts, his knowledge, his brain.
He cannot be relied upon for so great a task. Not unless we have exhausted all other options, and we have not.
This is the only way, Lae'zel. You know it just as well as I do.
All life is sacred. I will not let you hurt the githyanki.
So the githyanki lives, what then are you left with? What ideas remain untested?
I told you I sought only one thing - freedom. You have denied me this.
You have embraced transformation so far, but this would be a complete evolution.
In order to survive, I must now join the Netherbrain.

EditorData.logicalname: DOESNT HAVE ORPHIC HAMMER + RAPHAEL ALIVE

We hold the Hammer in hand, and you stood against me. Still - I see a path to ascension.

To think I trusted you. At best you are a ghaik pawn. At worst, you are a coward.

After you.

NO!

Hta'lak k'rith ma'har!

She is correct. Facing the Netherbrain without you would not be easy, but I will do it if I must.

EditorData.logicalname: Fallback if needed but shouldn't play on this path
